solutions.content:
Intuition:
There can be three kind of strings possible in logs:
"./", "../", "d/"
First Type  "./" :  In this type we don't need to move anywhere so don't do anything.
Second Type "../": In this type we need to go back to previous directory so remove last entry from stack(if stack contains any entry).
Third Type "d/":  In this type we need to move to next directory so push new entry into stack.
In the end return the position of final directory from root directory which is the size of stack.

Solution 1 using stack:

```
class Solution {
    public int minOperations(String[] logs) {
        Stack<String> s= new Stack<>();
        for(String log : logs) {
            if(log.charAt(1)=='.' && !s.isEmpty())  // pop only when "../" log is there and there should be some entry in stack.
                s.pop();
            else if(log.charAt(0)!='/' && log.charAt(0)!='.') //directory name can be anything so check for two conditions
                s.push(log);
        }
        return s.size();
    }
}
```




Solution 2: using single variable 

You can replace stack with simple variable. When you need to push new directory then just increment variable and when you need to pop then just decrement that variable. finally return the final directory position from root directory.

```
class Solution {
    public int minOperations(String[] logs) {
        int res=0;
        for(String log : logs) {
            if(log.charAt(1)=='.' && res>0)
                res--;
            else if(log.charAt(0)!='/' && log.charAt(0)!='.')
                res++;
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

