solutions.content:
Basic idea is to maintain depth of the current folder w.r.t. main folder.
As there are only 3 types of command then interpret and manipulate(+1, -1, 0) depth accordingly.
**Type 1** "./" : Depth will be same 
**Type 2** "../" : Decrease depth value by 1
**Type 3** "x/" : Increase depth value by 1

```
public int minOperations(String[] logs) {
        int depth = 0;
        for (String cmd : logs) {
            depth += interpretCurrentCMD(cmd);
            depth = depth < 0 ? 0 : depth;
            //Above condition will keep pointer in 
            //same folder if already in the main folder
        }
        return depth;
    }

    private int interpretCurrentCMD(String cmd) {
        // CMD Type "./"
        if (cmd.equals("./")) {
            return 0;
        }

        // CMD Type "../"
        if (cmd.equals("../")) {
            return -1;
        }

        // CMD Type "x/"
        return 1;
    }
```
