If you think of the directory hierarchy as a tree structure, this question is simply to figure out where you stand in the tree (the depth from the root or the main folder in this case) after performing all the operations in the logs array.

Having said that, we start from the main folder, where depth is 0. 

When encounter  "../", depth decrease by 1,  unless depth is at 0, then stay at 0; 

When encounter "./", do nothing. 

Otherwise, when encounter any other String, depth increase by one. 

At the end, the final depth value will be what it takes to return back to the main folder.

```
class Solution {
    public int minOperations(String[] logs) {

        int depth = 0;
        for (String s : logs)
        {
           if ("../".equals(s))
           {
              depth = depth == 0 ? 0 : depth - 1;
           }
           else if ("./".equals(s));
           else
           {
               depth++;
           }
        }
        return depth;
    }
}
```

