solutions.content:
Number of operations to get back to main folder is equal to the number of levels we are away from main folder.
To keep track of number of levels (depth) we are in, let us use `res` variable.
`res = 0` for main folder.

```
class Solution {
    public int minOperations(String[] logs) {
        int res = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<logs.length;i++){
            String currOperation = logs[i];
			//If not home and back operation - We go back one level.
            if(res>0 && "../".equals(currOperation)) res--; 
			//If ./ or if (main folder and ../) we do nothing.
            else if(currOperation.startsWith(".")) continue;
			//If forward operation - We add one level.
            else res++;
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

