# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. --> We can use a stack to record the number of files away from main we are.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. --> We will pop from the stack when we need to go back and we can push to the stack when we move forwards.

# Code
```
import java.util.*;

class Solution {
    public int minOperations(String[] logs) {

        // we will use a stack to keep track of our distance from the main file
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();

        // we will check each operation and convert it to an "action"
        for(String op: logs) {

            // if operation is "go back" then we will pop a value of the stack
            if(op.equals("../")) {
                if(!stack.isEmpty()) {
                    stack.pop();
                }

            // if the operation is not "stay in place" and not "go back" then we will add to the top of the stack    
            } else if(!op.equals("./")) {
                stack.push(1);
            }
        }

        // we will return the size of the stack as that is the number of operations away from main we are.
        return stack.size();
    }
}
```

