solutions.content:
The idea is to allow 4 customers who have been waiting untill the ```i```th rotation is done  ( denoted by ```customers[i]``` )  and then, calculate the profit at every rotation while keeping two constraints 

First is  ->  _the wheel must have been rotated 'i' times before the ith iteration  
Second is  ->  maximum of 4 persons can board the gandola._

```
class Solution {
    public int minOperationsMaxProfit(int[] customers, int boardingCost, int runningCost) {
        //calculate profit at each step and then store max profit.

        int totalC = 0, nR=0, maxNR = 0, waiting=0, maxProfit = - (int) 10e9 ;
        for(int i=0 ; i<customers.length ; i++) {
            waiting += customers[i] ; 
            if(nR < i) nR = i;
            if(waiting > 0) {
                //fill max of 4 customers.
                int d = Math.min(waiting,4);
                waiting -= d;
                totalC += d;
                nR++;
                int p = totalC*boardingCost - runningCost*nR;
               //boarded d at round nR, profit booked = p;
                if(p > maxProfit){
                    maxNR = nR;
                    maxProfit = p;
                }
            }
        }

        while(waiting > 0){
           //fill max of 4 customers.
            int d = Math.min(waiting,4);
            waiting -= d;
            totalC += d;
            nR++;
            int p = totalC*boardingCost - runningCost*nR;
            //boarded d at round nR, profit booked = p;
            if(p > maxProfit){
                maxNR = nR;
                maxProfit = p;
            }
        }
        return maxProfit > 0 ? maxNR : -1;
   }
}

