Problem description is confusing, but...
If we look at the explanation of the example problem. It is clear that inheritance goes in a DFS order. Kind of like this->

King -> 1st Child -> If first child has childs -> ...
		-> 2nd Child -> If sencond child has childs -> ..
		... and so on..

So, we can easity implement the solution with DFS.
We just need to keep track of the dead ones.

If someone is dead from the inheritance list, we just don't add him to our return list.

