solutions.content:
Intuition

- Let's maintain a tree (map from node to children)
- DFS is perfect for this problem because it goes deep on one node before moving onto the next
- Note that we need to push onto the stack in reverse order so that the "firstborn child" (and their children) can claim the throne earlier than later-born children

```
class ThroneInheritance {
  constructor(kingName) {
    this.root = kingName;

    this.childMap = new Map();
    this.childMap.set(kingName, []);

    this.deaths = new Set();
  }

  birth(parentName, childName) {
    if (!this.childMap.has(parentName)) {
      this.childMap.set(parentName, []);
    }
    this.childMap.get(parentName).push(childName);
  }

  death(name) {
    this.deaths.add(name);
  }

  getInheritanceOrder() {
    const stack = [this.root];
    let result = [];
    while (true) {
      if (!stack.length) {
        break;
      }

      const node = stack.pop();
      if (!this.deaths.has(node)) {
        result.push(node);
      }

      // push onto stack in reverse order
      const children = this.childMap.get(node) || [];
      for (let i = 0; i < children.length; i++) {
        stack.push(children[children.length - 1 - i]);
      }
    }
    return result;
  }
}
```

