An optimal way to solve this problem is to down loop k and iterate the bit masks where there are just k 1-bits. Once such a bit mask passes the check, we can terminate the loop and return k.

There is an elegant trick to do that: 
```
// Iterate all the m-bit masks where there are k 1-bits.

int state = (1 << k) - 1;            
while (state < (1 << m))
{
    doSomething(state);

    int c = state & - state;
    int r = state + c;
    state = (((r ^ state) >> 2) / c) | r;
}
```

