solutions.content:
So, basically what we would be doing is try out all the combination of requests and for each combination check wheter the *indegree* and *outdegree* are same.

Suppose there are **k** requests so total `2^k ` combinations are possible,

So we iterate from *i = 1 to 2^k* ,(As min answer would be granting 0 requests so we set the ans = 0 and start i from 1) and check the set bits in i which represents the index of requests granted and we update the indegree and out degree  accordingly .

To iterate over all of the set bits we use `if( (i>>r) & 1 )`  where `r` ranges over all the indices of requests

To check indegree and outdegree we use  - 
`A[n] = {0};`
and for each `r` satisfying `if( (i>>r) & 1 )`  we update - 

```
A[requests[r][0]]++; // Indicating out degree
A[requests[r][1]]--; // Indicating in degree
cur_ans++; // To update the current number of granted requests
```

After that we check if` A[i] = 0; for all i ` if Yes then we update 
`ans = max(ans,cur_ans)`

CODE - 
```
    int maximumRequests(int n, vector<vector<int>>& requests) {
        int ans = 0 , k = requests.size() , R = 1<<k;

        for(int i=1;i<R;i++){
            int *A = (int*) calloc(n,sizeof(int));
            int cur_ans = 0;
            for(int r=0;r<k;r++){
                if( int(i>>r) & 1 ){ // Checking if r`th bit of i is set 
                    A[requests[r][0]]++;
                    A[requests[r][1]]--;
                    cur_ans++;
                }
            }
            int x;
            for(x=0;x<n;x++)
                if(A[x]!=0) // Voilation of indegree and outdegree
                    break;
            if(x==n) // For all indegree and outdegree is cancel each other
                ans = max(ans,cur_ans);
        }
        return ans;
    }

```

k - number of requests 
n - number of buildings
**Time Complexity** - The outer loop will run 2^k times and for each outer loop we have two loops running 
* 1st Loop - k times (for updating building combination)
* 2nd Loop- n times (for checking whether the combination is feasible or not)

So Finally it is **O( (n+k) * 2^k  )**.


**Space Complexity** - **O(n)** (For storing the indegree and outdegree in A[n])

