# Intuition
Bruteforce thinking. Take or Not take a request. We have two options for each request shown in figure below. Each node represents one request.

![1601.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/2c810248-8840-408a-9b0e-dd92631e359e_1688314470.4731557.png)

The above figure shows how our algorithm should work.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(2^M*N)$$
For each request, we have two conditions, we either take the request or not take it. So, there will be a total of $$2^M$$ requests. After $$2^M$$ requests, we will iterate the `inDegrees[]` array of $$N$$ buildings to check if this is a potential answer. This will require $$O(N)$$ time. So, totally $$O(2^M*N)$$ time will be required.
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(N+M)$$
We declared an array `inDegrees[]` of length $$N$$ to store the in degrees. So, this will require $$O(N)$$ space. But we are also performing recursion call on the **backtrack()** method. The maximum number of active stack calls to the method would equal $$M$$ (when all the requests call would be active). Hence, the total space complexity would be $$O(N+M)$$.
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```Java []
class Solution {
    int permits;
    public int maximumRequests(int n, int[][] requests) {
        permits = 0;
        backtrack(0, 0, requests, new int[n]);
        return permits;
    }

    void backtrack(int cur, int noOfPermitsGiven, int[][] requests, int[] inDegrees) {
        if(cur == requests.length) {
            for(int inDegree : inDegrees) {
                if(inDegree != 0) {
                    // we must have all the inDegrees equal 0
                    return;
                }
            }
            permits = Math.max(permits, noOfPermitsGiven);
            return;
        }

        // give permission for this request
        // update the degrees
        inDegrees[requests[cur][0]]--;
        inDegrees[requests[cur][1]]++;
        backtrack(cur+1, noOfPermitsGiven+1, requests, inDegrees);

        // do not give permission for this request
        // reset the degrees
        inDegrees[requests[cur][0]]++;
        inDegrees[requests[cur][1]]--;
        backtrack(cur+1, noOfPermitsGiven, requests, inDegrees);
    }
}
```
