# Intuition
This question can be solved by checking all the possible choices of requests and maximizing the number of requests choosed.

# Approach
1. In order to get all the possible choices, we will use bitmasking.
2. We know that the total number of possible choices is ```(1<<n1)```, so we will make a bit string for each number in ```0-(1<<n1)-1``` and if any index is ```1``` then we will pass the request corresponding to it. Here ```n1==requests.size()```
3. For the given constraints, the size of bitstring is set to 20 here.
4. ```bit``` is the string as bit string.
5. But we don't want all 20 bits we just want last ```n1``` bits.
6. So we will take another string ```p``` as a sub string of last ```n1``` bits of the ```bit```.
7. Also we will take a vector build of size ```n``` and initialize it with 0. Also take a variable ```int ans=0;``` which will count number of requests passed.
8. Now we will iterate in this new string ```p``` and if ```p[i]=='1'``` then we will pass the request. Also we will increase the value of ```ans``` by one.
9. Passing the request means we will decrease the value of ```build[a]``` and increase the value of ```build[b]``` by ```1```.
10. After this we will check if all the elements of build is 0 or not. Because we don't want overall changes in each builiding.
11. If the above condition is cleared, then we will maximize the number of requests passed. 
12. After iterating over all choices we will return the maximum value.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n*2^n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(n)$$


    **Please upvote if you liked!!!**


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maximumRequests(int n, vector<vector<int>>& requests ) {
        int n1=requests.size();
        int m=1<<n1;
        int maxi=0;
        for(int i=0;i<m;i++){
            string bit=bitset<20>(i).to_string();
            string p=bit.substr(20-n1);
            vector<int>build(n,0);
            int ans=0;
            for(int i=0;i<n1;i++){
                if(p[i]=='1'){
                    ans++;
                    build[requests[i][0]]--;
                    build[requests[i][1]]++;
                }
            }
            bool ok=1;
            for(auto ele:build){
                if(ele!=0){
                    ok=0;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if(ok){
                maxi=max(maxi,ans);
            }
        }
        return maxi;
    }
};
```

