solutions.content:
**M** = Number of requests, **N** = Number of buildings

**Runtime**: O(2^M)  **This is better than official solution because we do not need to process the array to see if all buildings are at 0 indegrees thanks to the `netDifference` variable**

**Space**: O(N + M), need N array and M recursive stack

``` java
class Solution {
    public int maximumRequests(int n, int[][] requests) {
        return maximumRequestsRecursive(n, 0, requests, 0, new int[n], 0);
    }

    private int maximumRequestsRecursive(int n, int requestNum, int[][] requests, int netDifference, int[] changeFromOrigin, int processedRequests) {
        // Base case: if all requests have been processed
        if(requestNum > requests.length - 1) {
            if(netDifference != 0) return -1;
            return processedRequests;
        }

        // Option 1: Ignore current request
        int ignore = maximumRequestsRecursive(n, requestNum + 1, requests, netDifference, changeFromOrigin, processedRequests);

        // Process current request
        int from = requests[requestNum][0];
        int to = requests[requestNum][1];

        changeFromOrigin[from]--;
        changeFromOrigin[to]++;

        // If the "from" and "to" are different
        if(from != to) {
            // Case where the loss in a person got us closer to 0
            if(changeFromOrigin[from] >= 0) {
                netDifference--;
            } else {
                netDifference++; 
            }

            // Case where the increase in capacity got us closer to 0
            if(changeFromOrigin[to] <= 0) {
                netDifference--;
            } else {
                netDifference++;
            }
        }

        // Option 2: Include current request
        int include = maximumRequestsRecursive(n, requestNum + 1, requests, netDifference, changeFromOrigin, processedRequests + 1);

        // Undo the changes made to changeFromOrigin array
        changeFromOrigin[from]++;
        changeFromOrigin[to]--;

        // Return the maximum between ignoring and including the current request
        return Math.max(ignore, include);
    }
}
```

