solutions.content:
1. Simple dfs backtrack approach would be to iterate over all the requests and perform the following two operations for each of the requests:
	1. Consider this request.
	2. Do not consider this request.
2. If we cosider a request, we have to decrease employee count by 1 in source building and increase it by 1 in destination building.
3. When we are done with all the iterations we can check if all builidings have 0 employee count (no extra employee and no less number of employees than before), If so, count all the requests that we considered and update the answer.
4. Now, it may happen that we are repeatedly operating at a state where all the previously considered requests are same and curr Request  (we are iterating at) is same too.
5. So, it's better to store these 2 parameters in dp.
6. to store previous requests, use bitmask as : 
	If we are considering curr request (i.e., index in requests array is *curr*)  
	```mask = mask | (1 << curr) ```
7. at the end, when we have traversed all the requests, check if building population condition satisfies, if so, count the number of 1 bits in our mask.
```
class Solution {
    int[] buildingPopulation;
    Integer[][] dp;
    public int maximumRequests(int n, int[][] requests) {
        buildingPopulation = new int[n];
        dp = new Integer[1 << requests.length][requests.length+1];
        return helper(0, 0, requests);
    }
    public int helper(int mask, int curr, int[][] requests) {
        if(dp[mask][curr] != null)  return dp[mask][curr];
        if(curr == requests.length) {
            for(int x : buildingPopulation) {
                if(x != 0)  return dp[mask][curr] = 0;
            }
            return dp[mask][curr] = count(mask);
        }
        int max = 0;
        buildingPopulation[requests[curr][0]]--;
        buildingPopulation[requests[curr][1]]++;
        max = Math.max(max, helper(mask | (1<<curr), curr+1, requests) );
        buildingPopulation[requests[curr][0]]++;
        buildingPopulation[requests[curr][1]]--;
        max = Math.max(max, helper(mask, curr+1, requests));
        return dp[mask][curr] = max;
    }
    public int count(int mask) {
        int res = 0;
        while(mask != 0) {
            if((mask & 1) != 0)   res++;
            mask /= 2;
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```
for M = requests.length
Time Complexity : O( M * 2^M  )
Space Complexity : O( M * 2^M )

