Intuition:
    Each building needs to have the same amount of incoming and leaving people.
    Some buildings may not qualify, we need to exclude some of the requests.

Algorithm:
* Try every subset(every combination),
  * if all buildings qualify
    * count max people who can relocate

```java
public int maximumRequests(int n, int[][] requests) {
	// number of all combinations or the requests
	int lim = 1 << requests.length;
	int max = 0;
	for (int i = 0; i < lim; i++) {
		max = Math.max(max, check(n, requests, i));
	}

	return max;
}

private int check(int n, int[][] requests, int banned) {
	// 0 - in, 1 - out
	int[][] count = new int[n][2];

	for (int i = 0; i < requests.length; i++) {
		if ((banned & (1 << i)) == 0) {
			// number of incoming number of people
			count[requests[i][0]][1]++;
			// number of leaving number of people
			count[requests[i][1]][0]++;
		}
	}

	int sum = 0;
	for (int i = 0; i < count.length; i++) {
		if (count[i][0] != count[i][1]) {
			// building does not qualify
			return 0;
		}
		sum += count[i][0];
	}
	return sum;
}
```

